featureType.name: SeamapAus_NBHL_macroalgae
featureType.title: Seamap Australia National Benthic Habitat Layer - macroalgae extent
featureType.abstract:
The Seamap Australia spatial data layer is a nationally synthesised data product of seafloor marine habitat data. Australian continental shelf benthic habitat layers in GIS format were collected from various stakeholders around the country.
This layer represents the MACROALGAE extent derived from the most current version of the Seamap Australia National Benthic Habitat Layer. This includes mixed vegetation classes in which macroalgae has been positively identified (e.g. seagrass/macroalgae).
